"a.无间断的，连续的 【英】 adj. 无间断的，连续的(co ntinuing without interruption) 【记】 in(不)+cess(停止)+a nt→不停止的→连续的 【同】 同根词：concession( 让步); cessation(停止) 【例】 Jane bores me with her incessant talking. adj. 无间断的; 连续不断的 【记】in不, cess = cease(v 停止; 终了), ant－连续不断的 【参】concession(n 让步); cessation(n 停止) 【反】interrupted(adj 中断的) 【记】in 不+ cessant停止 【相关】cessation 停止，cease 停止 incessant (adj.)  mid-15c., from Old French incessant (mid-14c.), from Late Latin incessantem (nominative incessans) ""unceasing,"" from Latin in- ""not"" (see in- (1)) + cessantem (nominative cessans), present participle of cessare ""cease"" (see cease). Related: Incessantly (early 15c.)."
